'''Christophe Michalak''' ({{IPA-fr|kʁi.stɔf mi.ʃa.lak|pron}}; born 22 July 1973 in [[Senlis]], [[Oise]], France) is a French Master [[Pâtissier]] (pastry chef), author and television presenter.

==Biography==
Michalak was born in Senlis, France.<ref name=Leiths>{{cite web|url=http://www.prueleith.co.za/news/who-is-christophe-michalak/#.U1ws2vldWSo |title=Who is Christophe Michalak? - Prue Leith Chefs Academy |publisher=Prueleith.co.za |date= |accessdate=2014-04-27}}</ref>
Michalak has stated that as a young child, he originally wanted to become an architect. However, at the age of 15, Michalak started his journey to becoming a pastry master.<ref name=Leiths />  Michalak studied for his certificate of professional excellence in pâtisserie at the trade school of [[Angers]].<ref name=ozap>{{cite web|url=http://www.ozap.com/actu/-dans-la-peau-d-un-chef-une-emission-cuisine-en-access-a-la-rentree-sur-france-2/447983|title="Dans la peau d'un chef" : Une émission cuisine en access à la rentrée sur France 2|work=ozap.com|accessdate=24 November 2014}}</ref>
In August 2013, Michalak married actress Delphine McCarty.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.parismatch.com/People/Television/Delphine-McCarty-la-douceur-de-Christophe-Michalak-508560 |title=Delphine McCarty, la douceur de Christophe Michalak |language=fr |publisher=Paris Match |date= |accessdate=2014-04-27}}</ref>

==Career==
After achieving his certificate of professional competence, at the age of 16, Michalak decided to learn his trade across the world.  Michalak has studied and worked in many well known restaurants and pâtisserie across the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.christophemichalak.com/|title=Official website|publisher=Christophemichalak.com|accessdate=24 November 2014}}</ref>

Michalak currently works with world-renowned chef [[Alain Ducasse]] at the three Michelin starred, Plaza Athenaeum in Paris.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dorchestercollection.com/en/paris/hotel-plaza-athenee/restaurants-bars/chefs-profile/christophe-michalak |title=Christophe Michalak &#124; Chef's Profile &#124; Hotel Plaza Athénée Paris |publisher=Dorchestercollection.com |date= |accessdate=2014-04-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140706111530/http://www.dorchestercollection.com/en/paris/hotel-plaza-athenee/restaurants-bars/chefs-profile/christophe-michalak |archive-date=2014-07-06 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>
1991 - 1993 | [[Hilton Hotels & Resorts|Hilton]] London and Brussels<br />
1993 - 1995 | [[Hotel Negresco]], Nice ([[Michelin Star|Michelin]] {{rating|2|3}})<br />
1995 - 1997 | [[Fauchon]], Paris<br />
1997 - 1998 | Kobe, Japan<br />
1998 - 1999 | [[Pierre Hermé]], New York<br />
1999 - 2000 | [[Ladurée]], Paris<br />
2000 | [[Plaza Athénée|Plaza Athenaeum]], Paris ([[Michelin Star|Michelin]] {{rating|3|3}})<br />
2007 | Paulette Macarons, Beverley Hills, California<br />
2013 | Michalak Takeaway, Paris

In 2013, Michalak set up a pastry training school, "Michalak's Master Class", in Paris.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.michalakmasterclass.com/|title=ChristopheMICHALAK.com|publisher=Michalakmasterclass.com|accessdate=24 November 2014}}</ref>

==Awards==
2005 [[World Pastry Cup|World Champion Pâtissier]] (as part of the French Team)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cmpatisserie-lyon.com/the-contest/the-palmares/palmares |title=Palmares - Coupe du Monde de la Pâtisserie - Lyon Finale 2013 |publisher=Cmpatisserie-lyon.com |date= |accessdate=2014-04-27}}</ref><br />
2013 Pastry Chef of the Year<ref>{{cite web|author=Fernando Toda |url=http://www.sogoodmagazine.com/pastry-blog/pastry-competition/christophe-michalak-elected-best-pastry-chef-of-the-year-by-relais-desserts/ |title=Christophe Michalak, elected best pastry chef of the year by Relais Desserts |publisher=Sogoodmagazine.com |date= |accessdate=2014-04-27}}</ref>

==Bibliography==
Michalak has authored five cookbooks and also published a collection of best recipes.
* Christophe Michalak, ''Les desserts qui me font craquer (Desserts I'm crazy about)'', Paris, Édition Plon, 2010 
* Christophe Michalak, ''Les chocolat qui me font craquer (Chocolate I'm crazy about)'', Paris, Édition Plon, 2011
* Christophe Michalak, ''Le gâteau de mes rêves (Cake of my dreams)'', Paris, M6 Éditions, 2012
* Alain Ducasse and Christophe Michalak, ''Best of Michalak'', Paris, 2013
* Christophe Michalak, ''Les meilleurs dessers de France (Best Desserts of France)'', Paris, [[Éditions Gründ]], 2013
* Christophe Michalak, ''C'est du gâteau (It's the cake)'', Paris, Éditions Gründ, 2014

==Television==
Michalak has headlined three cookery programmes on French television aiming to demystify the complexities of French Pastry and has also been involved in the French version of MasterChef.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.connexionfrance.com/french-pastry-champion-christophe-michalak-11298-news-article.html |title=French pastry champion Christophe Michalak on his work - The Connexion |publisher=Connexionfrance.com |date= |accessdate=2014-04-27}}</ref>

From February 2012 to June 2013, Michalak was the host of the programme 'Le gâteau de mes rêves (Cake of my dreams)', which was broadcast on the Téva Channel.

In July 2013, Michalak became a judge on 'Qui sera le prochain grand pâtissier (Who's the next great pâtissier') on the France2 Channel.

From September 2013, Michalak co-produced and presented 'Dans la peau d'un chef (In a chef's shoes)' for the France2 television channel.<ref name=ozap /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.france2.fr/emissions/dans-la-peau-d-un-chef/recettes/recettes-de-christophe-michalak|title=Recettes de Christophe Michalak|work=France2|accessdate=24 November 2014}}</ref>

